MAGIC PALACE tracked four to three wide, pressed around the far turn, but failed to keep pace nearing the lane, and held show thereafter. KIKI KRAZY was antsy in the post parade, then was bumped by an outer rival into an inner foe at the start, lacked speed in the four path, and faded around the far turn before surpassing stopping rivals. LOTSANDLOTSOFGOLD leaned in and bumped a rival at the start, trailed while rank around the first turn, and made little impact.
